    <div class="section">
        <h2>
            Healthcare Authorities</h2>
        <p>
            Where applicable at feature level, the Microsoft Health CUI Design Guidance and supporting Toolkit controls adhere to the guidelines defined by the following leading authorities in patient safety:
        <ul>
            <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.who.int/patientsafety/solutions/patientsafety/en/index.html" title="Link to World Health Organisation website (New Window)">
                The World Health Organization (WHO)</a> - provides patient safety solutions
            for the identification and re-design of care processes for the prevention of human
            error reaching patients</li>
        
            <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.npsa.nhs.uk/patientsafety/improvingpatientsafety/patientsafetyinitiatives/compendium" title="Link to National Patient Safety Agency website (New Window)"> National Patient Safety Agency (NPSA)</a> - provides a compendium of advice, alerts and best guidance practice relating to patient safety</li>
        </ul></p>
    </div>   
